VERSION().notice: Contract version specified in the Farcaster protocol version scheme.

add(address,uint32,bytes,uint8,bytes).notice: Add a key associated with fidOwner's fid, setting the key state to ADDED.         Can only be called by the keyGateway address.

addGuardian(address).notice: Add an address as a guardian. Only callable by owner.

bulkAddKeysForMigration((uint256,(bytes,.notice: Add multiple keys as part of the initial migration. Only callable by the contract owner.

bulkResetKeysForMigration((uint256,bytes.notice: Reset multiple keys as part of the initial migration. Only callable by the contract owner.         Reset is not the same as removal: this function sets the key state back to NULL,         rather than REMOVED. This allows the owner to correct any errors in the initial migration until         the grace period expires.

domainSeparatorV4().notice: Helper view to read EIP-712 domain separator.

freezeKeyGateway().notice: Permanently freeze the KeyGateway address. Only callable by owner.

gatewayFrozen().notice: Whether the KeyGateway address is permanently frozen.

gracePeriod().notice: Period in seconds after migration during which admin can continue to call protected         migration functions. Admins can make corrections to the migrated data during the         grace period if necessary, but cannot make changes after it expires.

guardians(address).notice: Mapping of addresses to guardian status.

hashTypedDataV4(bytes32).notice: Helper view to hash EIP-712 typed data onchain.

isMigrated().notice: Check if the contract has been migrated.

keyAt(uint256,uint8,uint256).notice: Return key at the given index in the fid's key set. Can be         called to enumerate all active keys for a given fid.

keyDataOf(uint256,bytes).notice: Retrieve state and type data for a given key.

keysOf(uint256,uint8).notice: Return an array of all active keys for a given fid.

keysOf(uint256,uint8,uint256,uint256).notice: Return an array of all active keys for a given fid,         paged by index and batch size.

maxKeysPerFid().notice: Maximum number of keys per fid.

migrate().notice: Set the time of the migration and emit an event. Hubs will watch this event and         cut over to use this contract as their source of truth after this timestamp.         Only callable by the migrator.

migratedAt().notice: Timestamp at which data is migrated. Hubs will cut over to use this contract as their         source of truth after this timestamp.

pause().notice: Pause the contract. Only callable by owner or a guardian.

remove(bytes).notice: Remove a key associated with the caller's fid, setting the key state to REMOVED.         The key must be in the ADDED state.

removeFor(address,bytes,uint256,bytes).notice: Remove a key on behalf of another fid owner, setting the key state to REMOVED.         caller must supply a valid EIP-712 Remove signature from the fid owner.

removeGuardian(address).notice: Remove a guardian. Only callable by owner.

setIdRegistry(address).notice: Set the IdRegistry contract address. Only callable by owner.

setKeyGateway(address).notice: Set the KeyGateway address allowed to add keys. Only callable by owner.

setMaxKeysPerFid(uint256).notice: Set the maximum number of keys allowed per fid. Only callable by owner.

setMigrator(address).notice: Set the migrator address. Only callable by owner.

setValidator(uint32,uint8,address).notice: Set a metadata validator contract for the given keyType and metadataType. Only callable by owner.

totalKeys(uint256,uint8).notice: Return number of active keys for a given fid.

unpause().notice: Unpause the contract. Only callable by owner.

useNonce().notice: Increase caller's nonce, invalidating previous signatures.
